.Dd June 2, 2026
.Dt SQ 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sq
.Nd queue songs in musicd
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Fl s Ar socket-path
.Op Fl x
.Op Fl 0
.Op Ar position
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
reads paths or song references from standard input and sends them to
.Xr musicd 1
through the Unix-domain socket at
.Ar socket-path .
.Pp
A song reference has the form
.Ar path Ns # Ns Ar chapter-id .
When an input line is only a path,
.Nm
expands all chapters in that file.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl s Ar socket-path
Connect to this
.Xr musicd 1
socket.
.It Fl x
Clear the queue before adding songs.
.It Fl 0
Include the active song when clearing or positioning.
.It Ar position
Insert songs relative to the queue position instead of appending them.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr musicd 1 ,
.Xr sf 1
